<br>
I wrote the director of this that it is very late notice to get something of this magnitude organized, but perhaps there might be some interested members willing to volunteer some time to participate in some capacity.  <br>
<br>
Here are my questions in <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">blue</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->: :<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">How many volunteers are you envisioning as your ideal?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Exhibit Hall: - I would prefer 2 guards for each of 3 active show entrances and 1 guard for each of the 4 passive show entrances.<br>
<br>
Thursday 7am – 10am – 3 entrances – 6 troopers<br>
<br>
Thursday – 10am – 6pm – 7 entrances  - 10 troopers<br>
<br>
Friday and Saturday – 9am – 10am – 3 entrances - 6<br>
<br>
Friday and Saturday – 10am – 6pm – 7 entrances - 10<br>
<br>
Sunday - 9am – 10am – 3 entrances - 6<br>
<br>
Sunday – 10am – 4pm – 7 entrances - 10<br>
<br>
Sunday – 4pm – 5pm – 3 entrances – 6<br>
<br>
Task: door control and badge checking<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Registration Area Crowd Control<br>
<br>
Thursday 7am – Noon – 3 troopers<br>
<br>
Friday and Saturday – 7am – 1pm – 3 troopers<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Roamers<br>
<br>
It is always good to have a few roamers. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Will they be working in conjunction with hired convention security staff?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->  Not directly, but alongside.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">How much time you would like the volunteers to spend on crowd control each day?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">See Schedule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Could this duty be shared between different volunteers on different days of the convention?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Yes</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Would you be interested in any other costumed Star Wars characters besides Stormtroopers? </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Absolutely</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Would you be interested in Jedi characters or other members of the Rebel Legion costuming group?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Sure</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Hi Kathy,<br>
I apologize for getting such a late start to this. <br>
Sorry!  We have outlined areas of need in red.  This is a minimum number - we'd be happy with as many stormtroopers as possible!  I've seen pictures of the group that marched at our Star Wars Celebration show in 2002 and it was so impressive!    It might also be fun if they wanted to be an &quot;honor guard&quot; type of thing for the costume contest, held Sat from 2-4.  We usually march the contestants around the convention center before and after the show so it would be really cool if they had a stormtrooper guard.  Basically we'll use as many folks as you can scrounge up with this really late notice.  I can't arrange badges in advance for them as we had to download our system onto servers and ship them.  They only need badges if they want to get in the exhibit hall or to buy event tickets.  So if they just want to walk around the convention center they wouldn't need them.  But for those who'd like to see the exhibit hall or play games in their free time, I will reimburse their badge costs.  Normally we ask all of our volunteers to put in 16 hours for badge reimbursement, but I will be a little more lenient with your folks if they're close to that.  <br>
Thanks,  Jonni</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">My message to Jonni this morning:<br>
<br>
<br>
Hi Jonni!  <br>
<br>
I am passing the request along to as many costuming folks as possible.  <br>
This is extremely short notice to put something together of this magnitude.  <br>
I will see if there are people available to help out in the key areas.  <br>
Last year for CII the volunteer staff organization and planning began many months before the event actually happened.  <br>
<br>
Perhaps there are some folks who are able to help now for GenCon.  <br>
<br>
I myself am participating as a contestant in the costume contest on Saturday, but usually most of the groups are around and in costume on Saturday, so there might be a possibility, if nothing else, to have several Stormtroopers escort the costume parade around the convention.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
501st Members:<br>
<br>
<br>
Please email me at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:tkvanb@midwestgarrison.com"> tkvanb@midwestgarrison.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--> if you are able to help for any of these duties.  </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
